<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former East German Doctor Dropped from Training Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Bernd Pnsold, a former East
German doctor, is being dropped from the training center used by
Austrian ski star Hermann Maier because of his convicting of
giving performance-enhancing drugs, according to the Austrian
news agency APA on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A Berlin court found Pnsold guilty of administering
performance-enhancing drugs to nine underage athletes from
1975-84 even though he knew the drugs were dangerous. Pensold was
fined 14,000 marks (8,200 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Over the weekend, the Austrian Skiing Federation stepped up
pressure on Maier to cut his ties to Pensold. The Obertauern
training center is not under the federation's jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Maier, double Olympic gold medalist and last season's overall
World Cup champion, has always rejected any doping allegations
and said he used Pensold as a performance analyst, paying for his
services out of his own pocket.
</P>
<P>
Pensold also rejected any doping accusations. "I would be an
idiot if I _ with the reputation I have _ gave drugs to Hermann
Maier," Pensold was quoted as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
