<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, December 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi leadership convened an urgent session on
Wednesday afternoon to discuss the situation after all U.N. arms
inspectors evacuated from the country, the Iraqi News Agency INA
reported.
</P>
<P>
INA said a joint meeting of the Revolutionary Commmand Council
and the ruling Baath Party, chaired by President Saddam Hussein,
discussed the measures Iraq would take to confront possible
U.S.-British air strikes against the country. (Iraq-Session)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- U.N. relief workers have begun to evacuate from Iraq
following the withdrawal of U.N. weapons inspectors, a reliable
U.N. source said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. source told Xinhua on condition of anonymity that the
first group of U.N. humanitarian staff had already left
Baghdad. However, the number is not immediately known. (Iraq-UN)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Palestinian National Authority (PNA) will suspend
the implementation of the Wye agreement, a senior official said
after the Israeli cabinet reaffirmed Wednesday its decision to
postpone the pending troop withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian negotiator Hassan Asfour said the PNA will hold an
emergency meeting to come up with a concrete plan to stop
carrying out its part of the latest deal, stressing that the
commitments must be mutual. (Palestine-Israel-Peace Accord)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Leaders from 12 East Asian countries held their second
informal summit meeting here Wednesday afternoon to discuss ways
of increasing cooperation in overcoming the current economic
problems facing the region.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by the leaders of the nine ASEAN
countries -- Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam -- plus China, Japan
and South Korea. (Hanoi-East Asia-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has
expressed his support for holding early elections, Israel Radio
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The radio quoted several sources close to the prime minister as
saying that Netanyahu has decided to hold early elections and will
announce his plan before Monday, the day when the parliament is
scheduled to vote on a no-confidence motion on the government.
(Israel-Election)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Nine people have been officially confirmed killed by a
five-story apartment building which collapsed here early Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
A child was among the victims pulled out of the razed building,
which housed five families with a total of 38 people. The number
of victims is expected to rise because no one has been found alive
in late morning. (Italy-Building-Collapse) 
</P>
</TEXT>
