<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Highway Construction in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Wednesday
announced the approval of a 200 million U.S. dollar loan to China
for construction of the 152-kilometer-long Hefei-Anqing
expressway.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the Hefei-Anqing expressway is the main
component of the Anhui provincial highway project. This year
expressway would link the two major cities in the province and
eventually be part of two longer expressways in China's national
trunk highway system, linking the low-income province to the
markets of the coastal region and its deepwater ports.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, 240 km of existing provincial highways would
also be widened and rehabilitated to keep up with the area's
rapidly increasing congestion.
</P>
<P>
The overall project cost is some 453.9 million dollars. The
Chinese government will contribute 253.9 million dollars for the
project. 
</P>
