<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Prime Minister Leaves for OAU Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi left here Wednesday for Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso to
attend the summit of the Central Organ of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU) Mechanism for Conflict Prevention, Management
and Resolution.
</P>
<P>
The seven-month Ethio-Eritrean border dispute is one of the
items on the agenda of the two-day summit which convenes Thursday
in the Burkinabe Capital.
</P>
<P>
The OAU High Level Mediation Committee on Ethio-Eritrean
border dispute is expected to submit a report on proposals for a
settlement of the dispute to the Summit.
</P>
<P>
The summit of the OAU mediation committee on Ethio-Eritrean
border dispute, held in Ouagadougou on November 7 and 8, came up
with a set of proposals on the peaceful solution to the border
dispute. Ethiopia accepted the OAU proposals while Eritrea
rejected the key element of the OAU peace plan that calls for the
withdrawal of its troops from the disputed Badme area.
</P>
<P>
OAU Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim made an unannounced
visit to Eritrea last Saturday and held talks with President
Isaias Afworki.
</P>
<P>
Other items on the agenda of the two-day summit include the
conflict problems in the Democratic republic of Congo, Comoros,
Burundi and Sierra Leone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
