<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia, Iran to Boost Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Saudi-Iranian Trade
Committee concluded its two-day session Wednesday after reaching
an agreement on boosting economic and commercial cooperation
between the two countries, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The committee agreed on encouraging investment in joint
projects and holding commercial exhibitions in both countries,
according to the final minutes of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
A Saudi trade exhibition will be held soon in Iran, the
minutes said.
</P>
<P>
The committee also discussed means of promoting cooperation
between the Saudi Arabian Basic Industries Corporation and the
private Iranian Petrochemicals Company, it said.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of a navigation line linking Saudi and
Iranian ports was also discussed during the meeting, the minutes
said, adding that Iran has expressed readiness to transit Saudi
products to central Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Saudi Arabia, once in mistrust to each other for
almost two decades, began to improve their relation since Iranian
President Mohammad Khatami took office last year.
</P>
<P>
The two countries saw a big boost in their ties since last
February when Iran's former president Ali Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani paid a 14-day official visit to Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
Hence, the two sides have exchanged a number of other
high-level visits, during which talks on ways of boosting
bilateral ties and shoring up the sagging oil prices were held.
</P>
</TEXT>
