<HEADLINE> Primakov </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Russia is interested in seeing
more Swiss investments flowing into its economy, Russian Prime
Minister Yevgeny Primakov said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with the visiting Swiss President Flavio Cotti,
Primakov said that Russia will create the most favorable
conditions for foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
Russia is interested in direct investments in industry,
agriculture and the banking system, the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
