provide the necessary guarantees and conditions for the inflow of
investments to Russia."
</P>
<P>
At the meeting Primakov and Cotti discussed international
issues. They agreed that Russia and Switzerland are undoubtedly
interested in the stabilization of the situation and a peaceful
settlement of all existing conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Primakov and Cotti also signed a joint statement on further
development of cooperation in the fields of economy, environmental
protection, trade, investments and humanitarian aid.
</P>
<P>
Cotti arrived in St.Petersburg on Tuesday and arrived in Moscow
on Wednesday on a three-day official visit. He is expected to meet
with Russian President Boris Yeltsin on Thursday. 
