<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Ocalan to be Put on Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The United States said on
Wednesday Kurdish guerrilla leader Abdullah Ocalan should be
brought to justice and must not be set free.
</P>
<P>
"The United States believes that Ocalan should be brought to
justice for the terrorist crimes of which he is accused in a
manner consistent with international standards," said U.S. State
Department spokesman James Rubin.
</P>
<P>
"If he (Ocalan) is allowed to go free without facing charges it
would be a blow to the international fight against terrorism," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The United States had been in contact with senior levels of the
Italian, German and Turkish governments to express the view that
Ocalan should not be set free, Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Wednesday, Rome's Court of Appeals said Ocalan could
go free because Germany had withdrawn its international arrest
warrant and possible extradition request -- the only reason Ocalan
was detained in Italy. Germany had wanted him arrested for alleged
crimes on its soil.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan, leader of the outlawed Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK),
is also wanted in Turkey on treason charges.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish government holds Ocalan and the PKK responsible for
the deaths of more than 29,000 people killed by Kurdish fighters
and Turkish armed forces in the Kurds' 14-year fight for
self-rule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
