<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Organization Departments Commemorates Historical Meeting Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese party
official said here today that China has reexamined and reversed
4.18 million frame-up, false or wrong cases over the past two
decades.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Quanjing, head of the organization department of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made the
remarks at a seminar held here today to mark the 20th anniversary
of the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central Committee, which falls
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Outlining six major achievements China has made in
organizational work, Zhang said more than 21 million party
officials have attended theoretical study sessions since 1993.
</P>
<P>
The average age of officials at Party and government leading
bodies at provincial, prefectural and county levels have been
lowered by seven, six and five years respectively. At present over
93 percent of leading officials are college or university trained.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, the central committee has launched a campaign to
overhaul and consolidate grassroot party organizations in rural
areas and state-owned enterprises and achieved good results, Zhang
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
