<HEADLINE> Czech Rada Returning Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Czech defender Karel Rada is
leaving Turkey's Trabzonspor to join Slavia Prague on loan for
the second half of the Czech league season, according to reports
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Rada said he was moving back to the Czech Republic to be close
to his wife, who is expecting twins in February.
</P>
<P>
"I tried football abroad and now I'm quite looking forward to
playing in the (Czech) league again," Rada was quoted by the
Mlada Fronta Dnes daily as saying.
</P>
<P>
Hapal helped the Czech Republic team to qualify for Euro 96
but suffered a complicated leg fracture ahead of the finals in
England and has not played a league match since then, reports
said.  
</P>
