<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Condemns US Attack on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
Thursday condemned the U.S. attack on Iraq, terming it as an act
of "international terrorism."
</P>
<P>
"The Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan sees and condemns any
violent act which harms innocent civilians as an act of
international terrorism against peace and stability in the world,"
a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan quoted a statement by
the militia as saying.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the U.S. attacked Iraq as President
Bill Clinton was in need of an excuse to divert attention from his
possible impeachment.
</P>
<P>
The attack has provoked the wrath and indignation of the
world's Muslims, the statement said. 
