<DOCNO> XIE19981217.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Editorial Hails Anniversary of Landmark CPC Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Tomorrow's edition of People's
Daily, the voice of the Communist Party of China CPC), will carry
an editorial hailing the importance of the Third Plenum of 11th
CPC Central Committee held in 1978.
</P>
<P>
The editorial reviews the fundamental changes in various social
sectors over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
It also cites the historical merits of the Third Plenum of the
11th CPC Central Committee's decisions on establishing the Maxist
ideological line of "emancipating minds" and "seeking truth from
facts", as well as its decision to discard the erroneous principle
of "taking class struggle as the key link".
</P>
<P>
The editorial clarifies a number of political, ideological and
theoretical issues regarding problems lingering from the "Cultural
Revolution" and formulation of the reform and opening policies.
</P>
<P>
Monumental changes have taken place in China over the past two
decades under the guidance of the line, principles and policies
adopted during the Third Plenum.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese economy, which was once on the verge of collapse,
currently ranks seventh in the world in terms of gross domestic
product. The country leads the world in output for major
manufactured goods and farm produce, and ranks second in both
foreign exchanges and the use of foreign direct investment. In
addition, annual income levels for both urban and rural residents
have increased significantly.
</P>
<P>
The editorial attributed achievements over the past 20 years to
Deng Xiaoping, the architect of China's economic reforms. "The
achievement of today's good situation and new life for Chinese
people would have been impossible without Deng Xiaoping at the
core of the collective leadership of the second generation,"
according to the editorial."
</P>
<P>
It notes that the third generation leadership with Jiang Zemin
at the core serves as a link between the past and future, and
continues to lead the Party and people of all ethnic groups in
efforts to follow a correct line.
</P>
<P>
A number of new problems cropping up in the course of
modernization have required the staunch leadership of the
Party. Events in the late 1980s and early 1990s, especially the
Asian financial crisis and the devastating summer flooding, have
proved the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core is
fully capable of overcoming all difficulties. The efforts have won
the full support of the Party, army and people of all
ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The editorial calls on all Chinese citizens to rally around
Jiang Zemin and the Central Committee, unswervingly adhere to the
Party's basic line, join in efforts to combine reform and
development with stability, and work diligently in all fields to
greet the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's
Republic of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
