<HEADLINE> Sino-Portuguese JLG Agrees on Macao's Joining Int'l Bodies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Officials of the Sino-Portuguese
Joint Liaison Group (JLG) said here on Thursday that the two sides
have reached satisfying consensus on Macao's joining international
organizations and conventions.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xi'an and Moitinho de Almeida, Chinese and Portuguese
representatives of the JLG, met on Wednesday and Thursday
discussing Macao's joining international organizations and
conventions.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Moitinho de Almeida gave his Chinese
counterpart a final list of the international organizations which,
the Portuguese side thinks, Macao has joined and should remain
inside after the handover next year, and those which Macao should
join in after 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese side also submitted six international
conventions to the Chinese side, holding the view that they should
remain applicable in Macao after the handover.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that Macao can take part in meetings
convened by the International Civil Aviation Organization in the
name of a special administrative region of the People's Republic
of China.
</P>
<P>
A significant achievement of the two-day meeting was that the
Portuguese side has completed submitted the lists of Macao's
joining international organizations and conventions, Wang Xi'an
said, adding that the two sides will exert more efforts in this
regard. 
</P>
