<HEADLINE> HK Remains World's 3d Largest Foreign Currency Reserve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) announced that the official foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong were 88.6 billion U.S. dollars at the end of
November 1998, virtually unchanged from end-October's 88.7 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Including unsettled forward contracts, the foreign currency
assets of Hong Kong were also 88.6 billion U.S. dollars. The
figure was 88.5 billion U.S. dollars at the end of October.
</P>
<P>
In terms of foreign currency reserves ranking, Hong Kong
remains the third largest in the world, after Japan and China's
mainland.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets of 88.6 billion U.S. dollars
represent over seven times the currency in circulation or about 40
percent of Hong Kong dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the
world.
</P>
<P>
In November, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
Government announced the merger of the assets of the Land Fund
into the Exchange Fund at a consideration based on the market
value as at October 31, 1998. Henceforth, the announcement of the
foreign currency figure will be on a consolidated basis using the
assets of the enlarged Exchange Fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
