<HEADLINE> Macao Issues Chinese Language Proficiency Certificates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Passing the Chinese language proficiency
test, the first of its kind held in Macao, 52 people obtained
certificates of different degrees on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The test is aimed at examining the proficiency of Chinese among
those use Chinese as a foreign language or a second language. Most
of the 56 examinees were Portuguese or Macao-born Portuguese, and
others who come from Canada, Australia and Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Putonghua (standard Chinese) Training and Testing
Center under the Macao Polytechnic Institute organized the test on
November 7.
</P>
<P>
The China National Chinese Proficiency Test Commission examined
the test papers and conferred the certificates.
</P>
<P>
"The test was carried out in accordance with (China's) national
standard and the certificates are acknowledged around the world,"
said Sheng Yan, director of the center.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the test will greatly push forward Chinese
teaching in Macao.
</P>
<P>
"The most pressing matter at present is a more thorough
theoretical research on the test, so that it becomes more
reliable, effective, practical and authoritative," Sheng Yan said.
</P>
<P>
The second Chinese proficiency test in Macao will be held in
July next year. 
</P>
