<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Prison in China Develops Towards Civilization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- "This prison ranks first among
13 prisons I've visited in foreign countries in terms of
environment and management," according to Jeremy Corbyn, a member
of the British parliament.
</P>
<P>
Corbyn made the remark during a visit to the Beijing No.1
Prison in Daxing County located in the southern suburbs of the
Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The prison has hosted visits by 187 delegation and 4,291
individuals since 1996. The visits have provided people from both
at home and abroad with a good opportunity to learn more about
prison management in China.
</P>
<P>
Warden Yang Di noted the transportation of convicts has been
carried out over the past 16 years without a single incident. No
escapes have been recorded over the past two years, and the
recidivism rate is less than two percent.
</P>
<P>
The prison has adopted modern scientific measures to integrate
supervision, education and labor. The facility also provides
training which enables prisoners to adapt to the life on the
outside.
</P>
<P>
Yang noted that staffers assess the performance of inmates
daily on a 10-point system. The system is based on four points for
work performance, three for study habits and three for
behavior. The results are posted on a monthly basis and determine
the level of privileges granted.
</P>
<P>
The prison has also opened a school enabling prisoners to
pursue advanced studies. Some 119 inmates have passed national
college entrance examinations.
</P>
<P>
The facility, established in 1982, covers an area of 440,000
square meters and is staffed by 384 guards. The prison houses
close to 2,000 inmates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
