Thursday strongly condemned the United States and Britain for
their air strikes against Iraq, which have so far killed at least
five people and injured 30 others in Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the party urged an immediate end to the
"aggressive" military actions.
</P>
<P>
The statement said it is totally groundless for the two
countries to launch such military attacks when possibilities have
not yet exhausted for a peaceful settlement of the Iraqi weapons
inspection crisis.
</P>
<P>
