through military means, are flagrant trampling of Iraq's
sovereignty and international norms.
</P>
<P>
The party expressed deep sympathy for the Iraqi people,
especially women and children trapped in the current plight. The
party also promised moral and political support for them.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and British launched airstrikes, code-named Operation
Desert Fox, against Iraq early Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The strikes came shortly after chief U.N. weapons inspector
Richard Butler issued a report on Tuesday, claiming that Iraq was
not cooperating fully with the U.N. inspectors. The inspectors
evacuated Baghdad on Wednesday. 
