<HEADLINE> Regional Economic Meeting Starts in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials from member
countries of the Bangladesh-India-Myanmar-Sri Lanka-Thailand
Economic Cooperation forum (BIMST-EC) began a two-day session here
Thursday, to finalize the agenda of the ministerial meeting of the
sub-regional grouping scheduled for Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The officials would consider the report of the chairman of the
BIMST-EC working group, which was set up to coordinate the
activities of the member countries and covered six areas - trade
and investment, technology, transport and communications, energy,
tourism, and fishery, a Foreign Ministry press release said.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh assumed the chairmanship of the working group on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the second ministerial meeting of the BIMST-EC, to be
inaugurated by Foreign Minister Abdus Samad Azad, state or deputy
ministers of the five countries would set up an economic forum
comprising representatives of both the public and private sectors
to expand areas of cooperation among members of the bloc.
</P>
<P>
The BIMST-EC, a sub-regional grouping, was formally launched in
Bangkok, Thailand in June 1997 to promote economic cooperation
among three members of the South Asian Association for Regional
Cooperation (SAARC) and two members of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN). 
</P>
