<HEADLINE> First Buick Car Turned Out in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The first Buick car produced
by the Shanghai General Motors Co., a Sino-American joint venture,
rolled off a production line here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing today's ceremony, Hu Maoyuan, president of the
Shanghai General Motors Co., said the production line will officially
start operation in April next year with an initial annual output
of 50,000 units. The output will climb to 100,000 in three or four
years.
</P>
<P>
The company, the largest Sino-American venture in China, has
opened branches in Beijing, Guangzhou, Shenzhen and Shantou cities
apart from its base in Shanghai. It has turned out 200 Buick cars
with parts imported from abroad. They were immediately sold and in
great demand.
</P>
<P>
A market survey shows that 40 percent of the buyers were
foreign-funded firms, 30 percent were private firm owners and the
rest were government institutions and individuals. 
</P>
