Cem also disclosed that U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright phoned Turkish President Suleyman Demirel at 22:30 local
time (2030 GMT) Wednesday and conveyed him a message from
U.S. President Bill Clinton about the air strikes against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The strike took place at about 2200 GMT, midnight in Iraq with
a declared aim to destroy Iraq's military capability.
</P>
<P>
But Cem pointed out that the U.S. has not requested to use
Incirlik base in southern Turkey's Adana province.
</P>
<P>
The multinational forces led by the U.S. used the base to
bombard northern Iraq during the 1991 Gulf War. 
