<HEADLINE> Slovakia Supports U.S. Air Strikes Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard
Kukan on Thursday said Slovakia supports taking very tough
measures to prevent Iraq from producing weapons of mass
destruction.
</P>
<P>
Kukan said in a statement that the Slovak government hoped the
U.S.-led air strikes would pressure Iraq to change its current
stance of not cooperating with United Nations arms inspectors.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister expressed the hope that the strikes would
make Iraq start constructive dialogues with the international
community, as required by relevant U.N. Security Council
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain conducted air strikes against
Iraq in the early hours Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
