<HEADLINE> Causes of Baoji Fires Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Public Security Bureau in
Baoji, Shaanxi Province, held a press conference today to announce
what caused fires on November 19 and December 4.
</P>
<P>
The December 4 fire at the People's Department Store in Weibin
District killed eight and injured 24 people, according to a bureau
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said the rectifier on a third floor energy efficient light
fell during the night and ignited clothing on a mannequin. The
fire caused 4.17 million yuan in damage.
</P>
<P>
The November 19 fire at a wholesale market in the same district
was caused by a discarded cigarette butt. The fire destroyed
wholesale goods valued at 6.1 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
