<HEADLINE> Oman Regrets Over U.S. Strikes on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Omani Foreign Ministry
has expressed deep regret over air strikes launched by the U.S. and
Britain on Iraq Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman, who spoke on conditions of
anonymity, said that Oman is watching closely the development of
the situation and is concerned about the safety of civilians in
Iraq, the official WAM news agency of the United Arab Emirates
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Oman hopes that Iraq further demonstrates its willingness to
cooperate with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Britain launched the air raids shorlty after the
U.N. Special Commission, which oversees the disarming of Iraq's
weapons of mass destruction, reported that Baghdad failed to fully
cooperate with weapons inspectors.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Oman called on the international community to take
swift actions to ensure resumption of cooperation between Iraq and
the U.N. to end the crisis soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
