<HEADLINE> Egypt Values Relations with China: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
said on Thursday that Egypt attachs great importance to its
relations with China.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Yang Fuchang, China's outgoing ambassador
in Cairo, Mubarak said that Egypt and China maintain a
long-standing friendly relationship.
</P>
<P>
He said that he has been devoting himself to developing the
Egyptian-Chinese ties since he assumed the office of vice
president in 1976.
</P>
<P>
China has achieved a spectacular success in economic
development, which has caught the attention of the world, the
Egyptian leader said.
</P>
<P>
Egypt values the economic and trade cooperation with China,
Mubarak said, expressing hope that the two countries will further
enhance cooperation by widening the scope.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Yang Fuchang earlier met with Secretary General of
the Arab League Esmat Abdel-Meguid, who spoke highly of the
friendly relationship between the Arab world and China.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid expressed satisfaction with China's principled
stand of firm support for the Arab cause.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Arab League attaches importance to
promoting ties with China, expressing hope that China will play a
bigger role in advancing the Middle East peace process. 
</P>
