<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Rebound over 10,000 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed up
1.45 percent Thursday to break the 10,000-mark in futures-led
trade despite U.S.-British air strikes against Iraq, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng index gained 143.92 points to close at
10,083.31 on Thursday, after four consecutive sessions below the
mark.
</P>
<P>
The day's trade registered a low turnover of 2,963 million HK
dollars (379 million U.S. dollars), 201 million HK dollars (25
million U.S. dollars) up from the previous day's figure.
</P>
<P>
Many investors were believed to be more concerned with the
possible impeachment of U.S. President Bill Clinton. The air raids
had forced the U.S. House of Representatives Republicans to
postpone the debate originally scheduled for Thursday, on the
impeachment of Clinton. 
</P>
</TEXT>
