<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 72.48 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Thursday lost 72.48 points to
2,864.44 as against Wednesday's close of 2,936.92.
</P>
<P>
The national index also lost by 32.50 points to 1,267.86 from
the previous close of 1,300.36.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar were quoted lower at 294.05 and
115.05 compared with the previous close of 301.07 and 117.80
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities on BSE Thursday nose-dived due to reports of air
attack on Iraq jointly by the United States and Britain.
</P>
<P>
Activity was also affected by the procedural wrangles which
were likely to arise over the introduction of the Patents
(Amendment) Bill in the Upper House of Parliament. 
</P>
