<HEADLINE> S. Korea Enters Hockey Final in Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions South
Korea outscored Pakistan 3-2, moving to the final of the men's
field hockey at the Asian Games here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistanis, fielded in two players who featured in the
World Cup in May, scored the opner through Sohail Abbas in the
fifth minute through a penalty corner.
</P>
<P>
However, South Korea hit back with three quick goals to lead
3-1 at half-time before Abbas narrowed the margin midway through
the second half with another penalty corner.
</P>
<P>
South Korea will meet the winner between India and Japan,
looking for its third consecutive Asian title.
</P>
<P>
Two defensive errors took the match away from Pakistan as Jeong
Yong-Keun levelled in the 18th minute when his free hit from
outside the circle hit a Pakistani defender's stick and went in.
</P>
<P>
After Yeo Woon-Gon made it 2-1 in the 26th minute by deflecting
in a penalty corner, Pakistan failed to mark Kang Keon-Wook six
minutes later who cooly pushed in a pass from the right.
</P>
<P>
"In the end, it was those two mistakes that cost us a place in
the final," said Pakistani coach Shahnaz.
</P>
<P>
South Korean coach Koo Jin-Soo said he was looking forward to
winning the final to gain a direct entry into the 2000 Olympics in
Sydney. 
</P>
