<HEADLINE> Women's Soccer Final Heads into Extra Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- DPR Korea held defending
champions China into extra time as the two teams played to a
goalless draw after 90 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team found a tougher team in DPR Korea than they
beat 2-0 at last year's Asian Championships. Thought the Chinese
took a upper hand in the match, they could not find the way to
tear up the DPR Korea's defence line.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korean team could have won the match within the 90
minutes as their free-kick hit the cross-bar at the dying minutes
of the game. 
