<HEADLINE> Cholera, Diarrhea Claim 350 Lives in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 349 poeple have
died and 5595 others infected since September when cholera and
diarrhea broke out in some parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
In his work report to parliament Wednesday, Health Minister
Aurello Zilhao said that the worst-hit provinces are Cabo Delgado
and Nampula provinces in northern Mozambique, where 161 have died
of cholera and 114 of diarrhea since early last month, the
Noticias daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Over 15 died of and 891 infected with cholera in capital
Maputo and the nearby Matola since the eruption of the disease
last month.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that with the coming of the raining season,
the epidemic diseases may spread further in the country, where
some people had, with their own political motives, claimed that
the diseases were caused by poisoning of water by the government.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 have died of cholera since it broke out by the
end of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
