<HEADLINE> Paris Announces Bid for 2008 Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Paris said on Thursday it was
bidding for the 2008 Summer Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Paris Mayor Jean Tiberi made the announcement and said
Philippe Bourgignon, owner of the Club Mediterranee tourism
organisation, would head the bid's organising committee.
</P>
<P>
International Olympic Committee chairman Juan Antonio
Samaranch anticipated the announcement by telling reporters at
the Asian Games in Bangkok last week that Paris would bid for
third games of the next millenium. He was told over the telephone
by French President Jacques Chirac.
</P>
<P>
Paris, which held the games in 1900 and 1924, lost out to
Samaranch's home city of Barcelona for the 1992 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Other cities to bid for the Games are Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia,
Osaka, Japan, Beijing and Toronto, Canada  
</P>
</TEXT>
