<HEADLINE> Chinese Guan Wins Women's Long Jump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Guan Yingnan of China won the
women's long jump gold here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Guan, gold medalist of China's Eighth Chinese National Games
last year and the Asian Athletics Championships last July in
Japan, soared and landed for 6.89 meters in her last attempt. Her
teammate Yu Yiqun won the silver in 6.77, which was also produced
in the sixth jump.
</P>
<P>
The third place went to Yelena Pershina of Kazakhstan in 6.55.
She registered only two jumps in the six attempts.
</P>
<P>
Pershina took gold medals both at the 1993 Asian Championships
in Jakatar and at the East Asian Games last year in Pusan, South
Korea.
</P>
<P>
The 1-2-3 finish was just a repeat of that in the Asian
Championships last July in Japan, where Guan took the gold in
6.83, Yu finished second in 6.74 and Pershina third in 6.50.
</P>
</TEXT>
