<HEADLINE> Thai Boxer Claims First Boxing Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Suban Punnon outpointed
China's Yang Xiangzhong 14-1 here on Thrusday to take the first
gold medal in the boxing finals of the Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
In a five-round bout, the Thai resorted to defensive tactics
while his Chinese opponent took the agressive steps with neither
floored his opponent any time.
</P>
<P>
"The match is just so so," said Cuban coach G. Fontanialls
Quecaba,"he (Punnon) just wanted (the gold)."
</P>
<P>
Quecaba who coached the Thai boxer for the past four years and
returned to Bangkok two months ago from Cuba, remained silent with
any further questions.
</P>
<P>
"The judges had played the most in the final," said Wei Di,
director of the Chinese department in charge of the wrestling,
judo and weightlifting.
</P>
<P>
"Even if the Thai boxer could be crowned, the score can not be
in such a dominating way," Wei Di said, adding that "yet we're not
to protest the ruling anyway."
</P>
<P>
In the 12 boxing finals at the Asian Games, both Thailand and
Uzbekistan are aiming to vie for the supremacy in Asia with
Thailand having five final berths against seven for Uzbekistan.
</P>
</TEXT>
