<HEADLINE> Sabonis May Return to Lithunian Club </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Arvyda Sabonis of Portland
Trail Blazer center, may return temporarily to his home team in
Lithuania for the second round of European Euro-League play if
the NBA labour dispute continues, the team told Reuters IN
Vilnius on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"This is one possibility but I don't know for sure now. We
must wait about one week," Zhalgiris Kaunas General Manager Ginas
Rutkauskas was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Sabonis played for Zhalgiris Kaunas -- Lithuania's top squad
-- for about 12 years during the Soviet era, leaving in 1989 to
play for two Spanish teams.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, his last year before joining the NBA, he took Real
Madrid to the top of the European Champion Clubs' Cup.
</P>
<P>
He also led the Soviet Union's basketball team to a gold medal
in Seuol in 1988 and helped Lithuania bring home bronzes in 1992
and 1996.  
</P>
