<HEADLINE> CICB Sets Up Loan Department </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The China Industrial and
Commercial Bank (CICB) announced today that it has set up a
special department for offering loans and credit facilities.
</P>
<P>
Tian Ruizhang, vice-president of the CICB, said that the new
department will reinforce the bank's credit facilities and improve
the level of its credit assets.
</P>
<P>
"This is a significant measure for effectively preventing
financial risks and actively supporting the sustained, fast and
healthy development of the national economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the bank has played an important role in
supporting the technological progress of many Chinese enterprises
in the country's technological advancement and key construction
projects. Over the past 15 years it has extended loans of over 600
billion yuan to the fixed asset sector, providing support for more
than 170,000 advanced technology and infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The current outstanding amount of the bank's fixed asset loans
has reached 392.2 billion yuan, accounting for some 30 percent of
total such loans from state-owned banks.
</P>
<P>
Tian explained that the department would set up links with
other relevant departments in the bank and intermediate
institutions involved in providing credit facilities.
</P>
<P>
The bank has invited 45 financial experts to provide support
and professional consultation services for CICB's credit
assessment facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
