<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Winter Flu Packs Tianjin Hospitals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Hospitals in China's north
coast port city of Tianjin have been almost swamped with thousands
of patients after a major flu outbreak.
</P>
<P>
Now doctors are worried there may be a shortage of medicine.
</P>
<P>
At the city's Children's Hospital, long lines of sufferers
formed waiting to buy medicines or to be treated by doctors.
</P>
<P>
Harassed staff said the hospital has received more than one
thousand patients a day over the past few weeks, most of whom are
stricken by this latest strain of flu which has been sweeping
northern China.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from eight major hospitals in the city show that
more than 10,000 people have caught the flu in the last couple of
days. Some hospitals have warned that they have nearly exhausted
their supplies of flu medicine.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts said the flu epidemic has been caused mainly
by abnormal weather conditions, especially sudden changes of
temperature. Over the past four days, the mercury has stayed at
around 10 degrees Celsius, a rare phenomenon in this part of China
at this time of the year.
</P>
<P>
Other doctors at the Tianjin Disease Prevention Center fear
the flu virus might have come from abroad and might have slightly
mutated from the usual strain, making it more difficult to treat.
</P>
<P>
Doctors are now calling for more publicity to show people how
to prevent catching flu and are advising the increased use of a
flu vaccine to stop further outbreaks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
