<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Cracks Down on Fake Money Forgers, Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Three criminal gangs involved
in smuggling fake money have been smashed and police have seized
fake notes of over 80 million RMB yuan, 26.7 million U.S. dollars
and 180 million Marks, a senior official with the Ministry of
Public Security revealed today.
</P>
<P>
The crackdown took place in Heilongjiang Province in northeast
China, Guangdong Province in south China and Sichuan Province in
southwest China.
</P>
<P>
In September, police in Harbin, capital of Heilongjiang
Province, arrested six suspects who were charged with smuggling
fake Renminbi notes valued at 18.3 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in July, maritime police in Guangdong seized a fishing
boat from Taiwan, which was carrying 62.64 million worth of fake
Renminbi notes intended for distribution in the province. Another
seven suspects, from Taiwan and Guangdong, were arrested.
</P>
<P>
And, a death sentence was passed in September on Yang Jimao, a
smuggler of fake foreign notes in Sichuan. In his case, police
seized 26.7 million fake U.S. dollars and 180 million fake Marks.
</P>
</TEXT>
