<HEADLINE> Vietnam Urges U.S. to Stop Attack on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam Thursday described the
U.S. attack on Iraq as "a violation of Iraq's independence,
sovereignty and territorial integrity" and demanded that the
United States "immediately stop" its military action against the
Arabic country.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese Foreign Ministry said in a statement that the
Vietnamese government and people "are very concerned over the
military attack against Iraq."
</P>
<P>
"This action has seriously violated Iraq's independence,
sovereignty and territorial integrity and is running counter to
the U.N. Charter and international law," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"It has made the situation in the Gulf area more complicated
and tense and posed a threat to the life of the Iraqi civilian
population and it would lead to serious consequences," the
statement added.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government demands that the military action
against Iraq stop immediately and all differences be solved
through peaceful means in order to protect the interests of the
people of the Gulf countries and safeguard peace and stability in
the region, the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
