<DOCNO> XIE19981217.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Battle To Save Chinese Leukemia Student </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Help has been flooding in
from all over China, including Taiwan, for Chongqing university
student Zhang Yu who has leukemia and needs an urgent but very
expensive bone marrow transplant.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old senior student at Chongqing Normal College,
was only diagnosed with leukemia in October and was told that a
bone marrow transplant was the only cure.
</P>
<P>
With such treatment costing several hundred thousand yuan it
was out of the financial reach of Zhang's family who are only
salaried workers.
</P>
<P>
But several influential newspapers like Beijing Youth Daily and
Yangcheng Evening News in Guangzhou took up Zhang Yu's cause and
made him a household name. Since their campaign took off
nationwide donations have reached nearly two hundred thousand yuan.
</P>
<P>
Now the crucial search for a matching bone marrow donor is
under way but the probability of finding a match is only one out
in 10,000, according to medical experts.
</P>
<P>
Even with the help of reporters from the Chongqing Morning
Post and Yangcheng Evening News, who conducted a thorough search
of the Guangzhou Marrow Donor Registry, a suitable match could not
be found.
</P>
<P>
Finally an urgent plea was faxed to Taiwan's Tzu Chi Taiwan
Marrow Donor Registry which has a profile of more than 16,0000
donors.
</P>
<P>
The response was encouraging and preparations are now under
way to send samples of Zhang's blood for tests to Taiwan this
Friday, courtesy of the Macao Airline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
