<HEADLINE> Chinese President Calls for Stopping Military Action Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today urged the U.S. and Britain to cease military action against
Iraq so as to create conditions for the settlement of the issue
through dialogues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remark in his message to U.S. President Bill
Clinton, who sent a message to Jiang earlier today explaining the
U.S. stance on its military action against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Also today, Russian President Boris Yeltsin made a phone call
to Jiang, and Jiang said the U.S. use of force will bring severe
consequences to the situation in the Gulf region and the
international relations.  
