<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong
rose seven HK dollars to close at 2,708 HK dollars a tael on
Thursday, according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 293.40 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, up 0.76 U.S. dollars from the previous close at Thursday's
exchange rate of one U.S. dollar against 7.7475 HK dollars.
</P>
