<HEADLINE> Poland Says Attacks on Iraq Necessary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Polish government said
Thursday that it is necessary to take military actions against
Iraq after political means failed to solve the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi authorities had refused to implement the U.N.
resolutions and their cooperation with the U.N. Special Commission
had been suspended, said a government statement.
</P>
<P>
In order to make Iraqi President Saddam Hussein adhere to
U.N. resolutions, it is necessary to take military actions, the
Polish Press Agency quoted the statement as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, Poland also held out hope that the actions will not
bring damage to the civilians.
</P>
<P>
Also on Thursday, Polish Foreign Minister Bronislaw Geremek
told reporters that he "deplored and was disappointed" over the
fact that the Iraqi crisis was not solved through political means
and the United States and Britain had to resort to force.
</P>
<P>
He did not say whether Poland would join the military actions
or not. 
</P>
</TEXT>
