<HEADLINE> Pak Calls for Immediate Halt to U.S. Strikes on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Thursday expressed
grave concern and regrets for the U.S. strikes against Iraq and
called for immediate halt to these strikes.
</P>
<P>
"We are deeply distressed over the sufferings caused to the
Iraqi people and the loss of civilian life and property in Iraq,"
said a press release by the Foreign Office Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan called for immediate halt to these strikes, it said.
"We feel the pain of the long suffering of the Iraqi people as a
result of continuing sanctions and repeated military strikes."
</P>
<P>
"Their hardships and tragedy must come to an end", it noted.
</P>
<P>
It said that "Pakistan believes in the peaceful resolution of
disputes and the avoidance of use or the threat of use of force."
</P>
<P>
"Pakistan, therefore, supports implementation of and compliance
with all U.N. Security Council resolutions on a non-selective and
non-discriminatory basis," said the release.
</P>
<P>
It said Pakistan urges the United Nations Security Council to
take urgent measures to find a solution of the issue through
diplomatic means instead of use of force.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, "Pakistan calls for ensuring the preservation of
Iraq's independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity and
immediate alleviation of the sufferings of the Iraqi people," the
release said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
