<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Games So Far So Good, Says OCA Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A top Olympic Council of Asia
official said here on Thursday the Asian Games had been a success
which only needed a "perfect ending".
</P>
<P>
Wei Jizhong, OCA's Sports Committee chairman, said highly of
the efforts of the Bangkok people to ensure a successful event.
</P>
<P>
"There were some problems with the Asian Games before the
start, but up to now, I can say that the Bangkok Asian Games are a
success," said Wei, who had visited the Thai capital almost every
month to monitor the preparation for the Games.
</P>
<P>
"Now we have already had a good start, we still need a perfect
ending. Everybody must work harder to make sure it is the best
Games ever."
</P>
<P>
Wei said that he was expressing his own views and OCA president
Sheikh Ahmad al-Fahad al-Sabah would make the final assessment
upon the conclusion of the Games.
</P>
<P>
"It's just my personal evaluation. The Sheikh will evaluate
how successful the Games are after the closing ceremony," he said.
</P>
<P>
We said the Asian Games was one of the best ways to promote
Asian sports.
</P>
<P>
"Ten world records and 48 Games marks have been set and about
29 delegation has won medal here up to Wednesday against 22 in
Hiroshima," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Bangkok Games has 36 medal sports and two demonstration
events.
</P>
<P>
"Many people have criticised the OCA, saying there are too many
sports or too many athletes," said Wei.
</P>
<P>
"But we've shown that the OCA policy is a correct one. We
prefer to look at it positively.
</P>
<P>
"The best way to promote sports or a sport in a country is to
win a medal at the Asian Games. If a government sees that its
country can win a medal, they will put in more money to develop
that sport." 
</P>
</TEXT>
