<HEADLINE> Darsha Beats Li Xuemei in 200m Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- K. Damayanthi Darsha of Sri
Lanka, gold medalist in the women's 400 meters, beat 100m champion
Li Xuemei in the 200m semifinals on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Darsha defeated Li in the last few meters since the Asian
record holder of China apparently slowed down her pace.
</P>
<P>
Darsha clocked 23.16 seconds against Li's 23.35, which was far
behind her Asian record of 22.01 run in the Eighth Chinese
Naitonal Games last year.
</P>
<P>
With the top three in each of the two groups qualifying for
Friday's finals, India's legendary P.T. Usha finished fourth in
the second group in 24.27 and was out of the contention.
</P>
<P>
The Indian veteran, who has crashed in the 100m and 4X100m
relay, has only one event of 4X400m relay left in her fifth Asian
Games.
</P>
<P>
"She is not in a good shape since she has an injury in her
leg," India's coach Hargovind Singh said.
</P>
<P>
Li, who overcame a fever and stomach problem to win the 100m on
Monday, said yesterday that there will be no problem for her to
win a third gold medal from the 200m event.
</P>
<P>
"After winning the two events of 100m and 4X100m, I've got more
confidence," she said. 
</P>
