<HEADLINE> Exports of China's Light Industrial Products Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Despite the negative impact of
the Asian financial crisis and this summer's serious flooding,
exports of China's light industrial products have grown
significantly this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Customs Office, the export volume reached
40.4 billion U.S. dollars in the first nine months of this year,
up 6.6 percent over the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the export valume of machinery and
electronic products hit 11.4 billion U.S. dollars, an increase of
7.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
An official from the State Administration of Light Industry
attributed the increase to efforts in making maximum use of the
best ways to export products and to Chinese companies seeking out
more overseas markets during the year.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the increase in exports was also attributed
to the opening of factories abroad and to the state allowing some
enterprises to export their products without interference.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that China has so far set up more than
300 factories in 30 countries, including the United States,
Germany, France and some Southeast Asian countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
