<HEADLINE> Iran Releases 375 Iraqi POWs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Wednesday released 375
Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs) captured during the 1980-88
Iran-Iraq war, bringing the number of released Iraqi POWs to
55,150.
</P>
<P>
Ahmand Safavi, an Iranian official in the western Kermanshah
province told the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) on Thursday
that the 375 Iraqi POWs were released at Khosrawi border point in
line with an agreement recently reached between Iranian and Iraqi
officials in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
He said representatives from the two countries from the
International Committee of the Red Cross were present at the
releasing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has so far set free 39,364 Iranian POWs since the
two neighbors started swap of POWs in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Iraq reached an agreement in January to step up
their efforts to solve the remaining issues between them.
</P>
<P>
In April, Iran swapped 5584 Iraqi pows for 319 Iranian
pows. Since may this year, the two sides also exchanged the
remains of several hundred Iranian and Iraqi soldiers killed.
</P>
</TEXT>
