<HEADLINE> Return of Macao Major Step Toward China's Re-unification, FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- China's resumption of the
exercise of its sovereignty over Macao is another major event in
the Chinese history after Hong Kong's return to the motherland,
marking a stride toward the country's eventual reunification.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi made the remark at the
routine press briefing here this afternoon in response to a
question on the significance of the coming one-year countdown of
Macao's return, which falls on December 20.
</P>
<P>
Since China and Portugal signed a joint declaration on Macao
Issue in 1987, Sun said, the two sides have worked in cooperation
for the implementation of the joint declaration and held
consultations on related issues as the stable transition of Macao
and smooth transfer of power, and the two sides have achieved
good results or made progress of varying extent on a series of
problems occurred during the transitional period.
</P>
<P>
He urged the two sides to enhance cooperation and accelerate
the pace of work in tackling all problems relevant to the transfer
of power.
</P>
<P>
At present, all preparatory work for the return of Macao has
been progressing in an "actively and orderly" manner, Sun said,
adding that with joint efforts of all parties concerned, the
stable transition of Macao and smooth transfer of its power can be
assured.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
