<HEADLINE> Vice President Hu: China Attaches Importance to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice President
Hu Jintao said here Thursday that China attaches great importance
to the development of friendship and cooperation with Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
"We also value highly the role Malaysia plays in international
and regional affairs," Hu said at a meeting with Malaysian Prime
Minister Mahathir Mohamad, according to a Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
Vice President Hu, who is here on a three-day official visit to
Vietnam, congratulated Mahathir on his country's success in
hosting the APEC Informal Leadership Meeting last month.
</P>
<P>
He called Mahathir an old friend of China's and expressed his
thanks to the Malaysian prime minister for his consistent effort
to develop friendship and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hu pointed out that Sino-Malaysian ties at present are
excellent and the two countries enjoy consensus on a wide range of
international and regional issues. The two countries have
maintained good coordination and cooperation particularly in
safeguarding the economic interests of developing countries, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He pledged China's efforts to ensure, together with Malaysia,
excellent bilateral relations continue in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Mahathir, who is here to attend the Sixth ASEAN
Summit, praised China's increasingly important role in
international and regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said it is precisely China's policy of not devaluating the
RMB yuan that has helped reduce the losses afflicted on Southeast
Asian countries by the financial crisis which hit the region last
year.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed China's proposal for dialogue at the level of vice
finance minister and central bank vice governor within the
framework of the meeting among leaders of ASEAN and China, Japan
and South Korea, and hoped that the dialogue will begin as soon as
possible for them to earnestly discuss how to reform the
international financial mechanism and monitor the short-term
capital flow and other issues.
</P>
<P>
He said Malaysia is ready to further strengthen ties and
cooperation with China in various fields. 
