Bosworthy called on South Korean Foreign Affairs and Trade
Minister Hong Soon-young to explain the background of airstrikes
and asked for Seoul's support, South Korea's Yonhap News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain conducted airstrikes against Iraq
in the early hours Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Iraq said five people were killed and more than 30 wounded in
the airstrikes and all victims were citizens.
</P>
