<HEADLINE> Lee Jin-Il Wins Men's 800m Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Asian record holder Lee Jin-Il
of South Korea clinched the title in the men's 800 meters at the
Asian Games here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Lee, gold medalist four years ago in the Hiroshima Games, timed
one mintue 46.56 seconds, far behind his record of 1:44.14 clocked
at Seoul in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean was banned for three years after testing
positive for banned drugs in 1995. He returned to track only last
years.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very happy to win the gold because this is the international
meet I participated since the ban was lifted last year, " Lee said.
</P>
<P>
Lee, 25, said he experienced the darkest time in his life when
he was banned.
</P>
<P>
"I was not guilty for doping," he said. "I just took some
medicine for headache and cough."
</P>
<P>
"Five meters in front of the finish line, I belive the gold is
mine," he said.
</P>
<P>
His compatriot Kim Soon-Hyung finished second in 1:46.61 and
Qatar's Abdul Abdulla third in 1:47.10. 
