<P>
Sergeyev was reportedly consulting Russian President Boris
Yeltsin in Moscow on his planned trip to the NATO headquarters in
Brussels.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister was scheduled to meet with his
counterparts from NATO member states and NATO Secretary General
Javier Solana and discuss with them the nuclear transparency and
military cooperation between the Cold War foes during their
one-day council.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Britain launched an overnight air strike
against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Russia and China expressed their strong opposition to the use
of force, while France deplored the attack which has no
U.N. mandate and Germany regretted the attack but blamed Iraq for
failing to cooperate with the international community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
