<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Air Strikes against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Thursday condemned the
use of force against Iraq and called for an immediate halt to the
U.S.-Britain military air strikes on it neighbor.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi said such
attacks will only worsen the hardships of the Iraqi nation and
lead to further instability in the region, the Islamic Republic
News Agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
"It is quite unacceptable for us that certain states launch
willful military attacks on a country," Asefi said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the U.N. Security Council to hold an emergency
session to end the crisis and prevent further deterioration of the
situation.
</P>
<P>
Iran by no means will accept disintegration of Iraq and
will never keep mum on such an incident, the spokesman stated.
</P>
<P>
He also called on Iraq to cooperate with the U.N. and
comply with the Security Council resolutions.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and British forces in the Middle East launched air
and missile attacks on Iraqi facilities early Thursday morning as
a punishment for Iraq's alleged failure to cooperate with the
U.N. weapons inspectors.
</P>
<P>
One of the missiles fired by the U.S.-British forces fell in
the Iranian city of Khoramshahr in southwestern Khuzestan
province which borders Iraq, but caused no casualties, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
So far the Iranian authorities made no comment on the
incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
