<HEADLINE> 26 Philippine Rebels Surrender to Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-six members of the rebel
Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) Thursday formally surrendered
to the government forces in Maguindanao, the Southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Maguindanao, 14 pieces of firearms
were also handed over to the government forces by the rebels.
</P>
<P>
A corresponding amount will be paid by the government to the
former rebels for their surrendered firearms, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
A surrender rite was held at the headquarters of the 78th
Infantry Battalion of the government army in Mileb, Barongis town,
the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The MILF has become the main rebel force in the country since
another rebel group -- the Moro National Liberation Front (MNLF)
-- signed a peace accord with the government two years ago. The
MILF is fighting for independence of Mindanao. 
</P>
