<HEADLINE> Test-Tube Twin of Different Sexes Given Birth in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese woman recently gave
birth to a boy and girl at Shanghai's Women and Infants
Health-Care Hospital No.1 who are the first test-tube twins of a
different sex in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
They were born on November 24. The girl weighed 2,800 grams and
the boy, 3,000 grams.
</P>
<P>
The woman had had one of her oviducts removed because of an
ectopic pregnancy and the other had been blocked by an illness,
and her husband had a low sperm count and they had failed to
conceive a child during 10 years of marriage.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, doctors at the hospital fertilized six eggs
from the mother with sperm from the father and transplanted
embryos into her womb.
</P>
<P>
The couple live in Nantong City, Jiangsu Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
