<HEADLINE> Palestinians Protest Against U.S. Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Palestinians demonstrated in
the West Bank Thursday morning to protest against the U.S. air
strikes against Iraq overnight but the Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) has not made comments on the military action.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of Palestinian youths in a refuge camp in the
Palestinian-ruled Bethlehem, where U.S. President Bill Clinton
visited Tuesday, burned U.S. flags while demonstrating in the
town.
</P>
<P>
In another West Bank city of Ramallah, Palestinians marched
on the streets to show their solidarity with the Iraqi people,
Jerusalem Media and Communications Center, a Palestinian news
service, reported.
</P>
<P>
