<HEADLINE> Shanghai Popularizes Sci-Tech among Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A safety plug that protects
people from electric shocks has got an international award for two
primary school students at Shanghai's Hetianlu Primary School.
</P>
<P>
School students in Shanghai have won 164 awards in science and
technology contests.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Municipal Education Committee has selected 25
schools for popular science courses. Changle Middle School is one
of the pilot schools that link science, technology, and society
with the latest scientific research developments like genetic
engineering that arouse students' curiosity.
</P>
