<HEADLINE> Sino-French Joint Venture for Railway Shock Absorbers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The French ALST company and a
Chinese locomotive enterprise recently set up a joint venture to
produce hydraulic shock absorber for trains.
</P>
<P>
According to their contract, this joint venture--the sixth in
China involving ALST -- will produce DISPEN brand shock absorber, a
French patented product widely used in all types of trains the
world over.
</P>
<P>
China has already imported over 30,000 of these shock absorbers
to improve safety and comfort on its railway trains. With this
new venture, the equipment can now be produced domestically.
</P>
<P>
ALST is the controlling shareholder in this venture with 51
percent of the equity, while the Chinese partner, a research
institute of the China Railway Locomotive &AMP; Rolling Stock
Corporation, holds the remaining stock. 
</P>
