<HEADLINE> E. African Passport to Be Launched Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Cabinet Minister
Nicholas Biwott has disclosed that the long-awaited East African
passports will be launched on January 4, next year.
</P>
<P>
Biwott said Wednesday that the passports were ready to be
issued but the exercise could not proceed due to technicalities
in the other two countries, namely, Uganda and Tanzania,
according to Daily Nation newspaper Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The issuance of the common passport had been delayed because
Uganda and Tanzania were yet to register and issue their citizens
with identification cards like their Kenyan counterparts, the
minister noted.
</P>
<P>
He said it was after the issuance of identity cards was
through that the new passports were supposed to be issued,
otherwise there was a risk of issuing the new document to aliens.
</P>
<P>
Biwott, who is the East African Cooperation and Regional
Development Minister, said cooperation among the three countries
had excelled with free movement of people across the borders.
</P>
