<HEADLINE> Russia Slams U.S.-U.K. Strikes Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Russia called for an
end to the on-going use of force against Iraq, saying that the
current crisis was "artificially created."
</P>
<P>
Sergey Lavrov, Russian permanent representative to the United
Nations, told a late-night session of the Security Council
Wednesday that the "unprovoked act of force" by London and
Washington "violated the principles of international law and the
U.N. Charter."
</P>
<P>
The statement came as Iraq was being subjected to massive
missile strikes which had resulted in casualties.
</P>
<P>
"Justification for today's unilateral act was based on the
report" presented by the Chairman of the U.N. Special Commission
(UNSCOM), Richard Butler, who said that Baghdad failed to fully
cooperate with U.N. arms inspectors.
</P>
<P>
Butler had presented "a distorted picture of what was taking
place in Iraq," Lavrov said. He had "grossly abused his authority"
and his action led to the deterioration of the situation in the
country.
</P>
<P>
"Russia was convinced that resolution of the Iraqi problem
was possible only through political and diplomatic channels and
the norms of international law," he said.
</P>
<P>
"There were Russian citizens in Baghdad, if their lives were
imperiled, there would be serious consequences," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
