<HEADLINE> Summary of Latin American Reactions to U.S. Strikes on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The following is the summary
of some Latin American nations' reactions to the U.S. air strikes
against Iraq:
</P>
<P>
GUATEMALA:
</P>
<P>
-- The Guatemalan government Wednesday called for peaceful and
diplomatic solutions to the Iraqi crisis following U.S. and
British airstrikes against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Eduardo Stein made the statement to the press
a few hours after the air attacks.
</P>
<P>
Hector Mario Barrios Celada, Minister of National Defense, said
he is keeping a close watch over the Gulf situation.
</P>
<P>
A local missionary official called the airstrikes a threat to
world peace, adding that they broke both world peace and
international efforts to maintain peace.
</P>
<P>
MEXICO:
</P>
<P>
-- Mexico regrets that diplomatic efforts have failed to solve
the Iraqi crisis, the Foreign Ministry said in a statement
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Mexico prefers sustained political means to the use of force in
solving the Iraqi issue, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The government is "watching with grave concern over the
developments in Iraq," said the brief statement.
</P>
<P>
NICARAGUA:
</P>
<P>
-- Nicaraguan president Arnoldo Aleman on Wednesday said he
deeply deplored the United State's attack against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"I deplore it, I believe there are democratic ways, a dialogue
or organizations like the United Nations where (problems) can be
resolved without bringing pain to any country," he said.
</P>
<P>
PERU:
</P>
<P>
-- Peruvian Foreign Minister Fernando De Trazegnies Wednesday
expressed his regret at the U.S. air strikes against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Although the details of the U.S. decision on the strikes are
not available, the United Nations Charter must be adhered to,
Trazegnies said.
</P>
<P>
Asked to comment on the matter, Peruvian President of Congress
Victor Joyway said any war affair is negative. The U.N. should
make its attitude clear on whether the U.S. could take military
actions or not. 
</P>
