<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Center Michael Olowokandi,
the No.1 draft in June by the Los Angeles Clippers, is looking at
Christmas with a different kind of anticipation than most Pepole.
</P>
<P>
Olowokandi has been considering offers to play in Europe as a
result of the league's labor dispute. Bill Duffy, Olowokandi's
agent, says if the players and owners don't reach an agreement by
Christmas, his client will sign with one of several Italian teams
that have contacted him.
</P>
<P>
"We're serious about it," Duffy said. "We'll just wait and see
what happens. There are some deadline issues because players have
to register for the Euro League by January 1. We're proceeding as
though the season will be canceled."
</P>
<P>
Duffy said an unnamed Italian team wanted to sign his clitent
last week. The team offered Olowokandi a contract with a five-day
out that would have allowed him to leave if the lockout ended
within five days of his signing.
</P>
<P>
If Olowokandi were to sign, it would be for the balance of the
season, and Duffy said he would be among the top-paid players in
Europe.
</P>
<P>
"I'm still hopeful there will be an NBA season," Olowokandi
said."I'm not going to give up until the last. A lot will be
riding on what happens the next few weeks.
</P>
<P>
"I'm disappointed. I didn't think it would come this far. I
believe that whenever you have a dispute, everything is
negotiable."  
</P>
