<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Auto Sector Continues to be in Recession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indian automobiles
industry continues to be in the clutches of recession This year,
'Business Standard' said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Poor performance during the six months this year ended
September, 1998 by Telco, the commercial vehicles major in the
country, came as further blow to the industry. The fallen in sales
and profits of Telco subdued the overall results of the auto
players.
</P>
<P>
The aggregate results of 15 automobile companies for the six
months showed a fall in sales by four percent compared with the
same period last year. Operating profits were down by 12 percent.
Rising interest cost by 19 percent pushed the gross profit down by
20 percent and net profit crashed by 39 percent.
</P>
<P>
Segment-wise classification showed that the commercial vehicles
(CVs) segment was hit badly. The sales of CVs showed a steep
decline of 18 percent with Telco falling by 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Profit margins of auto companies came under heavy pressure.
While operating profit margin fell to 12.9 from 14.2 percent,
gross margin declined to 9.5 from 11.4 percent and net profit
margin was down to 3.9 from 6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
