<HEADLINE> Bayern, Kaiserslautern Disappointed at Cup Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- German giants Bayern Munich and
Kaiserslautern were disappointed on Wednesday because the
Champions Cup draw made them meet in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
"It's not so good for German football that the two teams are
to meet now," Kaiserslautern captain Ciriaco Sforza said.
</P>
<P>
"You can't pick and choose who you want," said Bayern
president Franz Beckenbauer. "It's no longer international but
has a domestic character. It's because of this that there is a
push by the bigger clubs to have teams seeded so this sort of
thing can be avoided in future."
</P>
<P>
Bayern topped and dashed out of the Champions League's "Group
of Death" which included Manchester United, Barcelona and
Denmark's Brondby.
</P>
<P>
Last Sunday, Bayern beat would-be challengers Bayer Leverkusen
at home and headed the table.
</P>
<P>
Bayern defeated title-holder Kaiserslautern 4-0 in the
Bundesliga this season.
</P>
<P>
Kaiserslautern, which headed by Otto Rehhagel and ranked third
in the Bundesliga now, denied Bayern last season's Bundesliga
title.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have already met once in the quarter-finals of the
1979-80 UEFA Cup. On that occasion, Bayern went through after a
4-1 win at home and 1-0 defeat away. 
</P>
