<HEADLINE> Ex-Resistance Chief Appointed Deputy Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Former FUNCINPEC resistance
deputy commander Khann Savoeun has been appointed as first deputy
chief of general staff of the Royal Cambodian Armed Forces (RCAF),
a post vacated by Nhiek Bun Chhay who fled into resistance last
July.
</P>
<P>
Defense co-minister Tea Banh and Prince Sisowath Sirirath have
confirmed the appointment, the Commercial News reported Thursday,
which means that Khann Savoeun has received a promotion from major
general (two stars) to lieutenant general (three stars).
</P>
<P>
Sirirath said the appointment was made by King Norodom Sihanouk
earlier this month. The appointment saw Khann Savoeun jump ahead
of Deputy Chief of Staff Lieutenant General Meas Sophea, a
Cambodian People's Party (CPP) appointee, in the RCAF command
structure.
</P>
<P>
An analyst said Khann Savoeun, a former officer in the
FUNCINPEC-aligned resistance in the 1980s, is respected by both
FUNCINPEC and CPP commanders.
</P>
<P>
Khann Savoeun was the RCAF commander of the Siem Reap
town-based Military Region 4 when factional fighting broke out in
Phnom Penh in July 1997 between loyal security forces of CPP and
FUNCINPEC.
</P>
<P>
When the fighting began, Khann Savoeun fled Siem Reap town for
the Thai border outpost of O'smach, which became a resistance base
for FUNCINPEC before it joined the new government. 
</P>
