create TV station.
</P>
<P>
To bolster their marketing, English clubs Leeds United and
Manchester United have done so before Marseille.
</P>
<P>
The channel, called "OMTV", will be available over the
network of pay television station Canal Plus between 4 p.m. and 8
p.m. every day.
</P>
<P>
 Customers will pay six dollars a month. The channel is set
to begin transmission on January.
</P>
<P>
 In addition to merchandising, the channel will feature
news,
quizzes and replays of classic matches.
</P>
<P>
 The club is hoping to sign up 12,000 subscribers by the end
of 1999.
</P>
<P>
