<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fans Ready to Bounce NBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- If readers responding to
questions about the NBA lockout had their ways, the season would
be canceled now.
</P>
<P>
Of the more than 3,700 readers responding to questions about
the lockout on USA today, 71% said that the league should call it
quits.
</P>
<P>
When asked to describe their feelings about no NBA games being
played, 50% angry and 17% said they are frustrated. Only 8% said
they couldn't wait until the players get back on the court. The
NBA did not comment on the survey results.
</P>
<P>
"Upon seeing my life without the NBA, I like it," said
Nicholas Holman of Fort Worth. "I don't occupy myself with all of
the stars and keeping up with the teams. I thought I would really
miss the NBA, but I don't miss it one bit."
</P>
<P>
The NBA and its players union last met Saturday for 30
minutes. Nothing was resolved and no further talks were scheduled.
</P>
<P>
Should the season start, 69% of the readers said they would
not get back to their routine of reading about or watching the
same number of games.
</P>
<P>
"I'm playing in an indoor soccer league and improving my
physical and mental well-being," said Steve McGinley of
Framingham." I would like to thank all the NBA players for the
opportunity to refocus my energies toward improving myself."
</P>
</TEXT>
