The military action came as the Security Council was discussing
a report by chief U.N. inspector Richard Butler, who said that
Baghdad failed to fully cooperate with U.N. arms inspectors.
</P>
<P>
U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan, who was present at the night
session, left without taking any press questions. He said in his
first response to the military action, "It is a sad day for the
United Nations and for the world." 
