<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said Thursday that Italy deeply regretted the U.S.-led air
strikes against Iraq and demanded a rapid end to them.
</P>
<P>
The Iraq crisis should be resolved through political means by
the United Nations, Dini said.
</P>
<P>
Dini said he had phoned U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright and British Foreign Minister Robin Cook Wednesday night
after the first round of air strikes at Baghdad early on
Thursday. 
</P>
