<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Records Impressive Export Earnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's export sector
recorded an impressive 3.69 billion U.S. dollars of earnings
during the first 10 months of this year, 13 percent up from the
same period last year, Central Bank officials said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the same period last year the earnings were 3.26 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The officials said the performance was a direct result of
attractive incentives, which were offered in line with the
government's commitment to developing export-oriented industries
to create employment for youths.
</P>
<P>
Through these incentives industrialists were able to modernize
and upgrade their industries resulting in an overall increase in
productivity, said the bank officials.
</P>
<P>
From January to October, agricultural exports were 873.5
million dollars, 16 percent up from the 750 million dollars in the
same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Industrial exports contributed 2.74 billion dollars. The
decrease in other exports have been offset by the increase in
textiles and apparels, beverages and tobacco and leather and
rubber products, the officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
