UNITED NATIONS, December 16 (Xinhua) - The Iraqi ambassador to
the United Nations on Wednesday called for an "unconditional,
immediate cessation of the aggression" by the United States and
Britain against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an open session of the 15-member UN Security
Council, Ambassador Nizar Hamdoon demanded "an unconditional
immediate cessation of the aggression that is underway against
Iraq."
</P>
<P>
Hamdoon accused chief UN weapons inspector Richard Butler of
making a "distorted" report to the UN Security Council that
triggered the military action on early Thursday Baghdad time.
</P>
<P>
"The exaggerated uproar over the Iraqi weapons of mass
destruction is nothing other than a big lie. The other is that
Iraq poses a threat to its neighbors," said Hamdoon. 
</P>
