<HEADLINE> Hebei Province Abundant in Geothermal Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Geothermal energy and
mineral-water resources have been proved to be abundant along the
Hebei section of the Beijing-Kowloon railway line, according to
the north China's province experts.
</P>
<P>
The provincial geological department estimates that the
geothermal energy along this Hebei section can provide enough
energy for 20 million hectares of greenhouse planting and over 600
billion square meters of heating.
</P>
<P>
The mineral department experts point out that this section is
also more abundant in geothermal resources than any other place on
the Hebei Plains.
</P>
<P>
With geothermal energy, the hub city of Hengshui along the
railway line has been able to solve its heating problems, and the
city of Renqiu has developed 5,333 hectares of greenhouse flowers.
</P>
<P>
The Hebei section of the Beijing-Kowloon line has twelve
mineral-water sites approved by the state, and some of these spots
are also rich in iodine.  
</P>
</TEXT>
