<HEADLINE> 143 Die of Cold In Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 18 (Xinhua) -- Low temperatures in
several Mexican states have left 143 people dead as health
authorities implemented a special winter program for 1998-99.
</P>
<P>
The health ministry said on Wednesday that in the northern
state of Chihuahua, temperature had dropped to nine degrees
centigrade below zero while in neighboring Sonora state, it had
gone down to 2.5 degrees below zero in the past 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
Health authorities said they had opened 792 temporary shelters
and started distributing food in 764 centers. 
