<HEADLINE> Australia Fully Support Air Strikes on Iraq: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Australia fully supports the
air strikes by the United States and Britain on Iraq Thursday
morning, which were inevitable and unavoidable, Australian Prime
Minister John Howard said.
</P>
<P>
Howard said having seen the report of U.N. weapons inspection
chief Richard Butler on Iraq's failure to comply with U.N.
sanctions, he believed the U.S. and Britain were left with no
alternative.
</P>
<P>
"Now in those circumstances, regrettable though it may be - any
use of force is always to be regretted and is always a sad event -
I do not believe and the Australian government does not believe
that the United States and the United Kingdom have been left with
any alternative," Howard told reporters.
</P>
<P>
"This has been very much a case of it being unavoidable and
inevitable that if Iraq failed to comply with the earlier
undertakings then similar action to degrade Iraq's military
capacity ... would eventuate." 
</P>
