<HEADLINE> Capsized Boat Kills 10 in Guizhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A motor-powered boat on
Qingshui River in southwest China's Guizhou Province capsized on
December 13, causing ten deaths, including four children under ten
years of age.
</P>
<P>
Police in Jinping County, Guizhou Province, said today that the
diesel-engine wooden boat had 33 passengers on board while on its
way to the town of Jinping at about 2:00 pm on December 13, when
it struck some rocks at the river bottom and was disabled.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports said crew members may have been responsible for
the accident.
</P>
<P>
The boat overturned at 2:20 pm as the crew attempted to pole it
free, and all the passengers were thrown into the deep river water.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of two men, four women, and an eight-year-old girl and
three boys under 10 were recovered by local police.  
</P>
</TEXT>
