<HEADLINE> Germany Hopes Fast End to U.S. Attack Against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The German government expressed
the hope that the U.S. strikes against Iraq will end quickly as
soon as possibly.
</P>
<P>
A German government spokesman, Uwe-Karsten Heye said Thursday
the federal government regretted that it had come to use military
measures.
</P>
<P>
Heye said that the international community have repeatedly
called on Iraq to comply fully with the resolutions of the
U.N.Security Council. 
</P>
