<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts Painting Exhibition on Famous Mountain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- An art exhibition displaying
scenes of Huangshan Mountain, a famous tourist attraction in east
China's Anhui Province, by over 100 Chinese painters is currently
attracting visitors in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
During the show running from December 9-16, 137 paintings by
108 well-known contemporary Chinese painters including Liu Haisu,
Zhang Daqian, Dong Shouping, Guan Shanyue, and Huang Binhong are
featured. A photo album of the paintings has also been published
in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Located in southern Anhui, Huangshan Mountain was listed as a
World Nature Cultural Heritage by the United Nations Education,
Sciences and Culture Organization in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The mountain is famous for its unique pines, rocks, clouds and
springs.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will also travel to Beijing, and the cites of
Hefei and Huangshan in Anhui Province early next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
