<HEADLINE> Canadian Cyclist Receives Four-year Suspension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Cyclist Steen Madsen has
received a four-year suspension from the Canadian Cycling
Association for failing a random drug test.
</P>
<P>
The banned anabolic substance, Nandrolone, was found in
Madsen's urine sample provided November 11 in Edmonton.
</P>
<P>
An International Olympic Committee accredited lab in Montreal
provided the A sample analysis December 2. A positive result was
confirmed upon completion of the B sample analysis December 12.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Healy, executive director of the Canadian Cycling
Association, Said: "The Canadian Cycling Association's position
on doping is clear. We have a no-tolerance policy." 
</P>
</TEXT>
