<HEADLINE> Chelsea Draws Man United in English Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A late equaliser by Gianfranco
Zola gave Chelsea a point in a match against Manchester United at
the English Premier League on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Zola played a neat one-two with Uruguayan substitute Gustavo
Poyet before neatly clipping the ball over the advancing Peter
Schmeichel with only eight minutes left to continue Chelsea's
record of losing only twice at Old Trafford in their last 24
league games.
</P>
<P>
The classy strike cancelled out Andy Cole's opener which was
the highlight of a dire first period that saw referee Graham
Barber hand out five yellow cards -- all to Chelsea players.
</P>
<P>
Cole capitalised on some loose defending in the visitor's box
to drill home a low effort past Ed De Goey's right hand after
Nicky Butt's shot had hit his feet and bounced kindly for the
United forward.
</P>
<P>
United stay second in the league with 31 points, two behind
Aston Villa. Chelsea are third on 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
