<HEADLINE> France Regrets "Spiral" Which Leads to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- France has expressed its regret
over what it called the "spiral" which has led to the military
strikes by the United States against Iraq Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
A French Foreign Ministry communique said that France also
regrets the serious consequences the strikes would inflict on the
Iraqi civilians.
</P>
<P>
"France regrets that the Iraqi leaders have not shown enough
proof of the spirit of full cooperation which was demanded by the
memorandum of agreement of February 23, 1998, between the U.N.
Secretary General Kofi Annan and Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tarek
Aziz," said the communique.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum could have make possible a comprehensive
examination of the Iraqi disarmament, as was called for by the
U.N. Security Council resolution 1194, it added. 
</P>
