<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Remain In Black </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 16 (Xinhua) - European stock markets enjoyed
solid gains Wednesday helped by a surge in oil shares as mounting
tension in Iraq boost the price of crude.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark Brent futures traded 92 cents higher at
11.15 US dollars, after last week's lowly 9.60 US dollars, as US
forces stood poised in the Gulf for a possible attack.
</P>
