<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The United States began
airstrikes against Iraq at 0:49 a.m. local time (21:49 GMT) on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The attack came just one day after the United Nations Special
Commission on disarming Iraq pullout all its staff in Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
Ear-deafening explosions can be heard all over Baghdad and the
sky over the city was lit up by flares.
